      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PAW UELLA (3) was rewarded for her honesty after two minors on end with a deserved win last time, scoring at Geelong over 400m (22.61). Has performed well from this box with a win and three minor placings to her name from five starts. The one to beat again. BULL DURHAM (7) was popular in betting last start but disappointed when 2.5 lengths away in fourth (16.69). Was in the money the start prior. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from three starts. Has ability and a bold showing is expected. WHY NOT SEB (1) has a strong overall record having four wins and eight places from 18 starts but was out of the money last time when fourth (24.79) over 435m at Sale. Performs well off this draw. Looks well placed here and has the ability. Go well. ITHACAN GODDESS (8) is worth consideration.",
